    <p>• A group of for­mer rugby league play­ers are pre­par­ing to take le­gal ac­tion against the sport’s au­thor­i­ties over what they said was a fail­ure to pro­tect them from the health risks caused by con­cus­sions, The Times of Lon­don re­ported.</p>
    <p>Ry­lands Law had been ap­proached by 10 for­mer rugby league play­ers and the law firm is said to be at an ad­vanced stage in pre­par­ing a claim, with joint ac­tion ex­pected to be filed next year.</p>


